    "John Trapp": "And the time. ] Heb., Days; one of the shortest measures of time. Solomon `[char_Solomon_Ref]` { #Ec 3:2 } alloweth men a time to be born, and a time to die, but no time to live. Punctum est quod vivimus et puncto minus. { a } { a } Seneca.\nVer.\n42. And the time.] Heb., Days; one of the shortest measures of [v_Ecc_3_2] time. Solomon `[char_Solomon_Ref]` {#Ec 3:2} alloweth men a time to be born, and a time to die, but no time to live. Punctum est quod vivimus et puncto minus. {a} {a} Seneca.\nVer."
